  "title": "Japanese Teacher (Childcare) - Central [GC]",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Deliver fun and interactive Japanese language lessons designed for preschool and kindergarten children.</li>\n  <li>Build a supportive and inspiring classroom where children feel excited to learn and explore.</li>\n  <li>Use music, stories, games, and visuals to enhance engagement and language retention.</li>\n  <li>Keep track of attendance and observe each child’s learning progress.</li>\n  <li>Partner with other teachers and share updates with parents regularly.</li>\n  <li>Highlight and refer any children who may need extra learning support.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Experience teaching Japanese to young learners, preferably in an early childhood environment.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of child development and effective teaching approaches.</li>\n  <li>Patient, creative, and passionate about helping children learn.</li>\n  <li>Able to commit to scheduled working hours long-term.</li>\n  <li>Basic English skills to communicate with colleagues and parents.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
